==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monologue
<hw>Mon"o*logue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>monologue</ets>, Gr. <?/ speaking alone; <grk>mo`nos</grk> alone,
single, sole + <grk>lo`gos</grk> speech, discourse, <grk>le`gein</grk>
to speak. See <er>Legend</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A speech uttered
by a person alone; soliloquy; also, talk or discourse in company, in the
strain of a soliloquy; <as>as, an account in
<ex>monologue</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dramatic composition for a single
performer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monology</ent>⟦br⟧
